    <name>Step 3: Separate the goal from the means</name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Separate&amp;nbsp;the “how,” to
achieve or accomplish that goal from the goal itself.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Allowing for flexibility in how
to accomplish the goal,&amp;nbsp;empowers learners to make choices that
maximize their strengths, support&amp;nbsp;learning needs,
and&amp;nbsp;demonstrate&amp;nbsp;understanding.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ask yourself: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;How have I offered flexibility in
how my learners can work toward the goal?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;How have I empowered and
supported learners to choose the means they will use to achieve the goal?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/octae-icon-resources.png" alt="" width="66" height="64" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;Additional Resource&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;a href="https://lincs.ed.gov/sites/default/files/GaM%20Designing%20Assessment%20Template_LFPA11y.docx" target="_blank"&gt;GaM
Designing Assessments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/octae-icon-tryityourself.png" alt="" width="66" height="64" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;Try it yourself:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9639@$&amp;amp;forceview=1" target="_blank"&gt;Reflect
on how you use your instructional goals to design assessments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

